# Soft per-rollout wall-clock cap on the test_generation milestone loop. The
# loop is bounded by an iteration count, but each iteration can take many
# minutes when the agent is iterating, so a worst-case run can blow past 2h
# (observed: 3.6h on a single ansible task). When this deadline trips the
# loop terminates gracefully with whatever portfolio exists so far — better
# a degraded but bounded result than an unbounded one. Override via env var
# `APEX_TEST_GENERATION_ROLLOUT_WALLCLOCK_SECONDS`.
