        "Do not rely on helper-only, forwarding-only, plumbing-only, or symbol-visibility-only checks when nearby authoritative evidence defines observable behavior at the public surface.\n"
        "Do not satisfy the required happy-path, missing, malformed, or ordering coverage only through a helper, alias, wrapper, or sibling API.\n"
        "When the issue introduces an opt-out or narrow override, preserve the documented default behavior as a separate assertion-bearing case whenever the task evidence shows it matters.\n"
        "If one direct artifact already covers the required issue-surface axes, remove helper, alias, serialization, cache-roundtrip, or internal-state artifacts unless they protect a distinct independently documented public contract.\n"
        "If earlier-stage artifacts proposed a helper or alias, keep that coverage supplemental or exploratory unless the issue, docs, types, or visible tests independently expose it as the primary public surface.\n"
        "Do not import helper-specific payload filters, extra sibling keys, or sentinel fields into the direct issue-surface artifact unless docs, types, or existing tests independently require them.\n"
        "When nearby authoritative tests enumerate exact literal examples or parametrized value rows on the same surface, preserve those concrete cases instead of compressing them into one broader generalized example.\n"
